HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 976
By Jones J
A RESOLUTION to commemorate the Kurdish New Year's
celebration of Newroz.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pride in recognizing those
significant cultural observances that enrich our State and uphold cherished traditions; and
WHEREAS, Nashville is home to the largest Kurdish population in the United States,
with an estimated 15,000 to 20,000 Kurdish residents; and
WHEREAS, the Kurdish New Year's celebration of Newroz coincides with the Spring
Equinox and is a festival celebrating the beginning of spring; and
WHEREAS, the Kurdish Newroz, derived from the Kurdish words new and roz, meaning
"new day" or "new sun," marks the start of spring and symbolizes renewal, hope, and freedom
among the Kurdish people; and
WHEREAS, Newroz is considered to be the most important festival in Kurdish culture
and has come to represent new beginnings and an opportunity to support the Kurdish cause;
and
WHEREAS, typically falling on March 21st, Newroz traces its origins to ancient
Zoroastrian traditions celebrated for thousands of years and remains deeply rooted in Kurdish
identity and history; and
WHEREAS, this year, Newroz will be celebrated from March 21st to April 1st; and
WHEREAS, during Newroz, families and friends come together to enjoy traditional
foods, music, dance, fireworks, singing, and poetry recitations; and
WHEREAS, spring flowers, such as tulips, hyacinths, and pussy willows are cut; new
clothes are worn; and pottery is smashed for good luck; and
HJR0976
013546
- 1 -

WHEREAS, families often spend the day in the country enjoying nature and the fresh
growth of spring; and
WHEREAS, on the eve of Newroz in southern and eastern Kurdistan, bonfires are lit to
symbolize the passing of the dark season, winter, and the arrival of spring, the season of light;
and
WHEREAS, during the thirteen days after Newroz, families visit one another and the
graves of deceased relatives and seek to resolve any conflicts or misunderstandings carried
over from the previous year; and
WHEREAS, the observance of Newroz by the Kurdish community in Tennessee
underscores the strength and vitality of the cultural traditions that flourish within our State; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we join with Tennessee's Kurdish community in commemorating the
Kurdish New Year's celebration of Newroz, acknowledging its rich cultural traditions and
significance, and extending our warmest wishes for a joyful, meaningful, and hopeful new year
to all those who celebrate.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
